solutions.content:
We first go left-to-right, and collect `i` that has `time` non-increasing guards. We track those indices in `before`.

Then, we go right-to-left and do the same for non-decreasing guards. If `i` is also in `before` - it's a good day to rob a bank.

(though, any day to rob a bank is a bad day)

**C++**
```cpp
vector<int> goodDaysToRobBank(vector<int>& s, int time) {
    vector<int> before, res;
    int cnt = 0, sz = s.size();
    for (int i = 0; i < sz; ++i) {
        cnt = i > 0 && s[i - 1] >= s[i] ? cnt + 1 : 0;
        if (cnt >= time)
            before.push_back(i);
    }
    for (int i = sz - 1; !before.empty() && i >= 0; --i) {
        cnt = i < sz - 1 && s[i] <= s[i + 1] ? cnt + 1 : 0;
        if (cnt >= time && i == before.back())
            res.push_back(i);
        if (i <= before.back())
            before.pop_back();
    }        
    return vector<int>(rbegin(res), rend(res));
}
```

