# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
If there are at least time adjacent pairs that is non-incresing, then the last index of the element could be a candidate.

Similarly, we could find all indices satisfying the non-decreasing condition.

Since the for loop doesn't consider the first and last element if time = 0, return all indices, else return intersection of the two sets.
