Idea is quite similar to https://leetcode.com/problems/find-good-days-to-rob-the-bank/discuss/1623415/Python-Explanation-with-pictures-prefix-sum. but instead of 2 x loop, this solution is using 1 x loop hence better speed result.
```
class Solution:
    def goodDaysToRobBank(self, security: List[int], time: int) -> List[int]:
        if len(security)<2*time+1:
            return []

        l=0
        for i in range(time-1,-1,-1):
            if security[i+1]<=security[i]:
                l+=1
            else:
                break
        r=0
        for i in range(time-1,-1,-1):
            if security[time+i+1]>=security[time+i]:
                r+=1
            else:
                break
        ans=[]
        if l==time and r==time:
            ans.append(time)

        for p in range(time+1,len(security)-time):
            if security[p]<=security[p-1]:
                l=min(time, l+1)
            else:
                l=0
            if security[p+time]>=security[p+time-1]:
                r=min(time, r+1)
            else:
                r=0
            if l==time and r==time:
                ans.append(p)
        return ans
```

