Thoughts:
* use a 2D array to store: days before and days after
* We only care about the neighboring elements security[i-1] and security[i+1] because when i = i-1, we also check security[i-2] and security[i]
	Example: If we want to know how many non-increasing days before ith day
					We will check security[i-1] ... security[0]
					But for security[i-1], we also checked security[i-2] ... security[0]
					Thus, for security[i]  = security[i-1] (The num of non-increasing days at i-1th day) +1
* Finally, check if the **non-increasing days before ith day** and **non-decreasing days after ith day** is >= time.



```
class Solution {
    public List<Integer> goodDaysToRobBank(int[] security, int time) {
        List<Integer> result = new ArrayList<>();
        int[][] prePost = new int[security.length][2];
