# Complexity
- ## Time complexity:
1. The outer loop iterates N times, where N is the number of bombs (for(long long i=0; i<bombs.size(); i++)).

    Time complexity: O(N)
2. Inside the outer loop, there is a while loop that iterates until the    stack is empty.

3. The while loop can potentially iterate N times because each bomb can be visited at most once.
Therefore, the worst-case time complexity of the while loop is O(N).
4. Inside the while loop, there is an inner loop that iterates N times (for(long long j=0; j<bombs.size(); j++)).
Time complexity: O(N)
5. The total time complexity of the inner loop is O(N), and it is executed O(N) times (inside the while loop).
Time complexity: O(N^2)

Putting it all together, the overall time complexity is O(N) * O(N^2) = O(N^3).

- ## Space complexity:
1. The maxBombs variable requires constant space.

2. The visited vector is used to track visited bombs. It has a size equal to the number of bombs, so it requires O(N) space.

3. The s stack is used for the DFS traversal. In the worst case, when all bombs are visited, the stack can store N elements.

4. The space complexity of the s stack is O(N).
All other variables used within loops require constant space.

Putting it all together, the overall space complexity is dominated by the space used by the visited vector and the s stack, both of which can grow up to N elements. Therefore, the space complexity of your code is O(N^2), where N is the number of bombs.

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    int maximumDetonation(vector<vector<int>>& bombs) {
        long long maxBombs = 0;
        for(long long i=0; i<bombs.size(); i++) // O(N)
        {
            long long crrIndBombs = 1;

            vector<long long> visited(bombs.size(), 0); 
            stack<long long> s;
            s.push(i);
            visited[i] = 1;

            while(s.size())
            {
                long long node = s.top();
                long long rad = bombs[node][2];
                long long xCord = bombs[node][0];
                long long yCord = bombs[node][1];
                s.pop();

                for(long long j=0; j<bombs.size(); j++)
                {
                    if(!visited[j])
                    {
                        long long total = ((xCord - bombs[j][0]) * (xCord - bombs[j][0])) + ((yCord - bombs[j][1]) * (yCord - bombs[j][1]));
                        if (sqrt(total) <= rad){
                            crrIndBombs++;
                            s.push(j);
                            visited[j] = 1;
                        }
                    }
                }
            }

            maxBombs = max(maxBombs, crrIndBombs);
        }
        return maxBombs;
    }
};
```

