# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
We have a radius/range for each bomb and every bomb in that radius will explode that will start a chain reaction. This implies that we need to constuct a graph where adjecent nodes will be the bomb index in the range.

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
We'll construct a graph whose adj nodes will denote the coordinates of bomb which will explode if Ith bomb exploded.
Now we'll run a DFS on the graph we constructed and calculate the longest chain we have.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
O(n^2) + O(n^2)--> to construct the graph and run dfs for every node.

- Space complexity:
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
O(n^2) --> as we are constructing graph.

