# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
I think its easy to understand if we think that radius of all circle are same. In that case 
If we have 3 point A,B,C

A reachable to B
B reachable to A
C is not reachable from A, B

In that case, if we did not find C while exploring A then we will never going to find A while exploring C

so we can iterate all the bombs by maintaining single visit array and return maxValue.

Now the thing is complicated here because the radius are not same so if we 
we have 3 points A, B, C

A reachable to B
B reachable to A
C is not reachable from A, B

but it possible that C can reach to A and B. In that case while exploring C we can encounter A and B again. 

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->

In solution, If you can see I used two visited array. The outer one is for visiting all the bomb point. If i have explored B while exploring A then i don't need to explore B again. 

If I am exploring C and I found A then i have to explore A again. 

# Complexity
- Time complexity: O(V * V)
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity: O(V)
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
```
class Solution {
    public int maximumDetonation(int[][] bombs) {
        int max = 0;
        boolean[] visited = new boolean[bombs.length];
        for(int i =0; i<bombs.length; i++){
            if(!visited[i]){
                Queue<Integer> queue = new LinkedList<>();
                boolean[] currVisited = new boolean[bombs.length];
                queue.offer(i);
                int count =1;
                currVisited[i] = true;
                visited[i] = true;
                while(!queue.isEmpty()){
                    int index = queue.poll();
                    int[] curBomb = bombs[index];
                    for(int j=0; j<bombs.length; j++){
                        if(!currVisited[j] && isReachable(curBomb, bombs[j])){
                            visited[i] = true;
                            currVisited[j] = true;
                            count++;
                            queue.offer(j);
                        }           
                    }
                }       
                max = Math.max(max, count);
            }
        }        
        return max;
    }

    private boolean isReachable(int[] bombA, int[] bombB) {
        long dx = bombA[0] - bombB[0], dy = bombA[1] - bombB[1], radius = bombA[2];
        long distance =  dx * dx + dy * dy;
        return distance <= radius * radius;
    }

}

```

